Class EventHandling

  • java.lang.Object
    • EventHandling

  • public class EventHandling
extends java.lang.Object
    A class to handle all the events in the GUI. It also instantiates most of the other classes.

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        private void initialize()
        Is called when the GUI is created and sets up all the action handlers. It also loads the google maps page in the web engine window.

      • setUpServer

        void setUpServer()
        The method creates a task that blocks on serverSocket.accept(). When a connection is received within that task, a Server object is created to handle the connection. When the task created has finished running, it returns the reference to the accepted socket to the EventHandling class. The GUI is updated to show that a drone is now connected. A wpProtocol task is created to Strings are printed in the standard output telling the user what is happening.

      • newMissionItem

        private void newMissionItem(java.lang.String command)
        Called when either 'Fly to', 'Land' or 'Lift' are clicked in the GUI. It creates a mission item for the list in the GUI.
        Parameters:
        command - A string containing the mission item type.

      • clear

        private void clear()
        Clears the mission item list and send a message to the drone to clear its list as well.

      • start

        private void start()
        Not properly tested, but it seems like this method(the Mavlink command sent) jumps to the first takeoff mission item in the list and continues from there.

      • stop

        private void stop()
        Not properly tested, but it seems like this method(the Mavlink command sent) jumps to the first land mission item in the list and continues from there.

      • list

        private void list()
        Supposed to list the mission list currently in the drone, but it is added to the WpProtocol which from the beginning was something just meant to work, so somewhere in the horrible code, there is something wrong with this command sequence.

      • mission

        private void mission()
        Reads the list of mission items created in the GUI and tells WpProtocol to send it. It seems like the first mission item you send specifies the home position. In this case all 0's are used to take the current position where it starts. See the code for Mavlink parameter specifics.

      • status

        private void status()
        Tells the drone to send the status message stream req_stream_id at the rate req_message_rate. The Mavlink message used is officially deprecated, but it is the only one supported in the firmware used. See the Mavlink documentation for different stream IDs. For example https://pixhawk.ethz.ch/mavlink/ .

      • arm

        private void arm(int arm)
        Arms the drone if all the pre-arm checks are passed or they are disabled.

      • changeMode

        private void changeMode(int newMode)
        Changes the mode of the drone.

      • wifi

        private void wifi(double status)
        Send a message to the phone telling it to turn the wifi on or off.

      • current

        private void current()
        Not tested, but it should change the mission item currently active to the specified number in the mission item list.

      • send

        private void send(MessageType messageType,
                  byte[] mavLinkByteArray)
        Instantiates the Message class and fills it with the byte array and message type supplied and sends it to the drone.
        Parameters:
        messageType - The type of the message to be sent(either Mavlink to the drone or a command to the phone)
        mavLinkByteArray - The Mavlink message byte array if messageType is Mavlink
        See Also:
        MessageType
